comments: Gallinari (OKC) and Walker (BOS) briefly engage and separate off-ball.
Paul (OKC) makes marginal contact with Smart's (BOS) arm that does not prevent him from gathering the ball.
The ball does not make contact with the rim on Paul's (OKC) shot attempt at the buzzer.
Adams (OKC) sets the pick in Hayward's (BOS) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Theis (BOS) makes incidental high-five contact with Paul (OKC) after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Theis (BOS) makes marginal contact with Gallinari (OKC) as he releases from contact after the pick.
Theis (BOS) extends his leg, but he does not make leg contact with Paul (OKC) at the start of the drive.
Adams (OKC) is firming up in a picking position in Hayward's (BOS) path as he sets the pick, and he absorbs contact when contact occurs.
Tatum (BOS) cleanly blocks Schroder's (OKC) jump shot attempt.
There is no conclusive angle showing whether Dort (OKC) makes contact with Tatum's (BOS) arm during his driving shot attempt.
Tatum (BOS) makes incidental contact with Adams's (OKC) hand on the ball before cleanly dislodging the ball, and incidental arm contact occurs after Tatum dislodges the ball.
Walker (BOS) briefly grasps Paul's (OKC) jersey during his driving shot attempt but the contact is marginal.
Theis (BOS) sets the screen in Ferguson's (OKC) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Schroder (OKC) cleanly dislodges the ball from Walker (BOS) in the backcourt.
Paul (OKC) legally contests Tatum's (BOS) jump shot attempt.
Dort (OKC) and Smart (BOS) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Adams (OKC) cleanly dislodges the ball from Theis (BOS) before Theis begins his upward motion.
